      • getLatestCommitInfo

        public static org.eclipse.emf.cdo.common.commit.CDOCommitInfo getLatestCommitInfo(IBranchPoint branchPoint)
        Returns with the latest commit info representing the most recent change in repository on a specified branch. If there are no changes on the given branch, then the most recent change will be returned from the ancestor branch before the branch creation time.
        Parameters:
        repositoryUuid - the unique ID of the repository.
        branchPath - the branch path.
        Returns:
        the commit info representing the most recent change.

      • check

        public static boolean check(org.eclipse.emf.cdo.common.commit.CDOCommitInfo commitInfo)
        Returns with true if the argument can referenced and the commit info does NOT represents a failure commit into, hence the CDOBranchPoint.getBranch() can be referenced as well. Otherwise returns with false.
        Parameters:
        commitInfo - the commit info to check.
        Returns:
        true if the argument can be referenced, otherwise false.

        public static String removeUuidPrefix(String prefixedMessage)

      • removeUuidPrefix

        @Nullable
public static String removeUuidPrefix(String prefixedMessage,
                                                 boolean failFast)
        Extracts and removes the leading version 4 UUID if any from the prefixed string argument. Returns with the modified argument. This method might ignore extracting the leading UUID on the specified prefixed message argument if failFast is false. If failFast is true and the message argument does not contain a leading UUID, then this method throws a runtime exception.
